es that predictions at position i rely solely on known outputs at preceding positions. The attention function entails using the query, keys, and values to output a weighted sum of the values. Our specific 'Scaled Dot-Product Attention' efficiently computes this across queries, employing scaling to maintain softmax function efficacy over substantial dot-product magnitudes. Multi-Head Attention further enhances the model by executing multiple parallel attention mechanisms, enabling the model to concentrate on various representation subspaces concurrently. Each encoder and decoder layer also possesses a fully connected feed-forward network using two linear transformations and ReLU activation. Positional encodings integrate order information into these non-recurrent, non-convolutional layers, using sinusoidal functions to provide geometric progression in wavelengths.", "save_path": "rewritten_paper.pdf"}

